    "attributes": {
        "action": "Extend article 50 and call for a 'Citizen's Assembly' to resolve Brexit crisis",
        "additional_details": "The time has come that the decision is given back to the people, not by a divisive second referendum but a healing, and unifying Citizen's Assembly.\r\nA Citizen's Assembly worked very well in Ireland to heal the divide over abortion.",
        "background": "The Brexit debate has caused a deep societal divide in Britain which cannot be resolved by either pushing a 'no deal', 'no Brexit' or Teresa May's failed deal. A Citizen's Assembly, rather than a divisive second referendum, can heal this divide, but this needs time.",
